history.content:
Hm, I don't see them on classes.berkeley.edu.

But those sound like labs (based on time, room, and also numbering), not lectures.

children.subject: Maybe then its a mistake by Cal Central? Because it seems like the system would allow me to swap to this "lecture"

history.content: Thanks for flagging this.  This was a mistake. If the new scheduling system were any good, it would have been impossible to make that mistake but it was nonetheless my mistake and not done by Cal Centeral.  They should have been listed as labs.  They will be soon.  Unfortunately, that means students who signed up for those "lectures" will be purged (after being notified that they need to re-sign up via email).

children.subject:
Lol @ the salt: "If the new scheduling system were any good [...]"

+1, for what its worth

history.content:
New lecture sections were added to CS61A (67158, 148C, Mo 4:00PM - 5:29PM, Soda 275 and 67159, 149C, Mo 4:00PM - 5:29PM, Soda 277). What is the difference between these 1.5 hour lectures that meets once a week versus the main lecture (38652, 001, MoWeFr 12:00PM - 12:59PM, Wheeler 150) that meets 3 times a week for 3 hours total?

It seems to be strange to have a lecture that is half the length of the other.
